<article> UCIâ€™s Office of Inclusive Excellence, under its Confronting Extremism initiative, has issued a call for proposals to promote understanding about equity in the age of COVID-19. In addition to bringing to light some of the best qualities of ingenuity and empathy in individuals, the worldwide coronavirus crisis has exposed and exacerbated inequities in society. In this episode of the UCI Podcast, Douglas Haynes, vice chancellor for equity, diversity and inclusion, talks about the call for proposals with Sheri Ledbetter of the Office of Strategic Communications & Public Affairs. For more information, see https://inclusion.uci.edu. </article>
